OL,3,CCouncil dismisses plans to build homes
OL,4,Cexclusively for Welsh speakers
OL,6,FA landmark attempt to reserve a new
OL,7,Fsocial housing estate solely for Welsh
OL,8,Fspeakers has been dismissed.
OL,10,FThe Trefor and Llanaelhaearn Community
OL,11,FCouncil originally backed plans for 15
OL,12,Faffordable homes on the village's
OL,13,Feastern edge, but only on the
OL,14,Fcondition that occupants were "able to
OL,15,Fspeak Welsh."
OL,17,FThe local council described the
OL,18,Fproposal as a "golden opportunity" to
OL,19,Fbe the first in Wales to "venture to
OL,20,Fimpose a language condition on a new
OL,21,Fsocial housing estate."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/5
